ğŸ§  What are Getters and Setters?
ğŸ”¹ Getters:
Ye methods field ki value read karne ke liye hote hain.

ğŸ”¹ Setters:
Ye methods field ki value set/update karne ke liye hote hain.

â— Generally fields private hote hain (Encapsulation), aur unke access ke liye public getter/setter diye jaate hain.

âœ… Why Use Them Instead of Direct Access?
java
Copy
Edit
// âŒ NOT Recommended
public class Student {
    public String name;  // Direct access â€“ bad practice
}
Isse data unsafe ho jata hai, koi bhi change kar sakta hai.

Instead, use private fields + get/set methods â†’ âœ… Safe

âœ… Example: Getters and Setters
java
Copy
Edit
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;

    // Getter for name
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    // Setter for name
    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }

    // Getter for age
    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }

    // Setter for age
    public void setAge(int age) {
        if (age >= 0) {
            this.age = age;
        }
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();

        s.setName("Ravi");
        s.setAge(20);

        System.out.println("Name: " + s.getName());
        System.out.println("Age: " + s.getAge());
    }
}



ğŸ”¹ 1. Validation in Setter
java
Copy
Edit
public void setMarks(int marks) {
    if (marks >= 0 && marks <= 100) {
        this.marks = marks;
    } else {
        System.out.println("Invalid marks!");
    }
}
